      "lesson title": "Drone and Survey Data Risks",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "Drones and survey tools are increasingly used to collect mapping and inspection data across a wide range of industries, from construction and agriculture to infrastructure and environmental monitoring. When this data is inaccurate, incomplete, or poorly managed, it can lead to costly mistakes, safety risks, and poor decision-making. This lesson introduces the key risks associated with drone and survey data, including equipment limitations, human error, and data handling issues. By understanding where things can go wrong, you will be better placed to take practical steps to improve the quality and reliability of the data you collect and use. No prior technical knowledge is required, and the content is designed to be accessible and relevant to anyone working with or relying on drone and survey outputs.",
